Champions Liverpool proved themselves on Saturday when they hit seven goals past Crystal Palace at Selhurst Park. The Reds, coming from a 2-1 victory against Tottenham during the week, recorded their first away win in the English Premier League. They are now six points clear at the top of the Premier League table. Minamino, Sadio Mané, Roberto Firrmino, Jordan Henderson and Mohammed Salah got their names in the score sheet. Commenting at the end of the match, Liverpool Coach, Jurgen Klopp commended his boys, saying “this is a very good match, my boys proved themselves. Goal difference, this is good for us. Crystal Palace also had their moment. “This guarantees us to be amongst the top, which gives us a good Christmas.” Manchester United will go in search of their first Premier League win under manager Louis van Gaal when they travel to Sunderland on Sunday. If there was any doubt about the scale of the task facing the Dutchman, it was demonstrated by last weekend's 2-1 opening day defeat at home… August 22, 2014 In "Sports" The new Premier League season bursts into life this weekend with last season's top two, Manchester City and Liverpool, facing each other at Eastlands. Just three points separated the two sides last term and having both notched wins on the opening weekend, City and Liverpool will be keen to maintain… August 21, 2014 In "Sports" London   -    The form table suggests Liverpool have realistic hopes of disrupting Manchester City’s waltz towards the Premier League title when they meet on Sunday, although they must quickly learn how to cope without Philippe Coutinho. The Brazilian playmaker completed a 142 million-pound ($192 million) move to Barcelona on Monday,… January 11, 2018 In "Sports"